To all the people who replyed to my question,thank you.  You all seem to be very amazing people and yet even though each and every one of you has come from a different background you all manage to understand what the other is going through. I have read what you all had to say and realise that there is no right nor wrong. People need to talk and understand but accusing is not the answer,listening is. I realise now that all wars are horrific and that Vietam more so because of the lack of communication,soliders doing their duty for their country and anti-war people going about it the wrong way. You can never accuse a person of following what he believes only trying to understand and gain knowledge from his/her mistakes !<br>
Also thank you for all the mentioned books I have already gotten a hold of a few of them and am 'enjoying' reading up and gaining knowledge,as a wise man once said knowledge is power !!!<br>
Please carry on writting in.<br><br>
Steph
